  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.TextMeshPro::TMPro.TextMeshProUGUI
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: '<b>Included Scenes</b>


    The <b>Main</b> scene is the entry point
    of the package. It illustrates the basic usage of Scene Registry: how to reference
    a scene via a SceneReference and load it without ever using its name or index.


    The
    <b>Sample</b> scene is a demonstration scene designed to be loaded from the Main
    scene. It represents the typical use case of a real project: a game scene referenced
    safely and resistant to renaming.'
